By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Former President  Dr Goodluck Jonathan is now holding a closed door meeting with the Senate President,  Dr Bukola Saraki In Abuja.  Though the purpose of the meeting is not known as at the time of filing this report,  Sundiata Post reminds  that it may not be unconnected with the Saraki’s consultations of former Nigerian leaders.  Recall that the Senate President,  Bukola Saraki had in the last couple of weeks, visited former military president, General Ibrahim Babangida (rtd) and former president Olusegun Obasanjo In Minna, Niger State and Abeokuta, In Ogun state respectively.  The Senate President embarked on these visits shortly after dumping the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC)  and pitched tent with the Peoples Democratic Party,  (PDP) .  Senate President Bukola Saraki had in an interview recently with a foreign media said he is suggesting contesting against the incumbent President Muhammadu Buhari In the 2019 general elections.  Details  Later… 